From c52dca73944d32d4ca1d63299736661402de3e02 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 23:58:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate importlib startup hot paths

Hardware samples in the frozen-importlib phase found two dominant
cross-group loops.  typeobject.c's automatic group 132 repeatedly called
the group-7 slotptr and dictionary lookup paths from update_one_slot, while
codeobject.c's automatic group F3 repeatedly entered group-7 interning from
intern_constants.  Put both measured callers in group 7.

The rich-equality chain also crossed the automatic object and Unicode
groups.  Give the four measured comparison bodies a small explicit group 10
and return a new reference to the Boolean singleton directly instead of
leaving that path for PyBool_FromLong.

Keep the nearly-full initialization group within its 90,112-byte slot by
evicting five cold dictionary API bodies.  Their previous linked bodies
totalled 1,640 bytes, and moving the 296-byte unicode_compare_eq body to
group 10 frees 1,936 bytes.  update_one_slot and intern_constants total
1,940 bytes, so the measured 89,836-byte group 7 is predicted to grow by
only four bytes to 89,840 bytes, leaving 272 bytes.  The previous comparison
bodies plus a group header form a 2,364-byte upper bound for group 10 before
the direct-singleton simplification.  The post-link residency verifier
remains the authority for exact fit and membership.
